Within 3 years after a license has expired, the Board may reinstate the license if the licensee:
Was licensed by passing a Board approved national licensing examination;
Has not practiced physical therapy or limited physical therapy in this State during that period;
Otherwise is entitled to be licensed;
Pays to the Board the application fee set by the Board;
Submits to the Board an application on the form required by the Board; and
Has met the continuing education requirements of § 13-311(d) of this subtitle.
